# Obsidian vault sync (Wist)

When you make **substantive** changes to the app (features, architecture, roadmap-worthy behavior, notable refactors):

1. Update relevant notes under `ObsidianVault/10-Project-Wist/` — at minimum check [[Architecture]], [[Roadmap]], and [[Backlog]] when the change affects behavior users care about.
2. Add or adjust a **session note** in `ObsidianVault/10-Project-Wist/Sessions/` when the work is worth a dated record.
3. Do **not** duplicate full code in Obsidian; keep high-level bullets and links to modules/files.

Skip updates for trivial one-line fixes or purely cosmetic edits unless the user asks.
